HOW THIS SOFTWARE IS LICENSED  (read this first)

This software is made available under TWO separate instruments. You may rely
on whichever one grants you the permission you need for your specific activity:

  (a) the PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0 (full verbatim text below),
      which permits noncommercial use, study, modification, and sharing, and
      grants a NONCOMMERCIAL patent license; AND, IN ADDITION,

  (b) the MCL Security Research & Evaluation Grant
      (see the file SECURITY-RESEARCH-GRANT.md, also reproduced at
      LICENSES/LicenseRef-MCL-Security-Research-Grant.txt),
      which ADDITIONALLY permits ANY party — INCLUDING commercial and
      for-profit organizations — to download, compile, run, benchmark,
      reverse-engineer, cryptanalyze, and attempt to break this software, and
      to publish the results, free of charge, subject to a citation
      requirement, SOLELY for security research and evaluation (not for
      commercial production or integration use).

In plain terms:
  • Academics, students, nonprofits, and public institutions: you are covered
    by the PolyForm Noncommercial License for research, study, and teaching.
  • Companies and commercial security teams: you ARE permitted to evaluate,
    test, and try to break this software, and to publish your findings, under
    the Security Research & Evaluation Grant — at no charge.
  • Anyone who wants COMMERCIAL PRODUCTION OR INTEGRATION use (shipping it in a
    product or service, internal commercial deployment, offering it as a
    service): you need a separate paid commercial license. See COMMERCIAL.md.

PATENT NOTICE: The methods implemented here are the subject of pending patent
applications. See PATENTS.md. A noncommercial patent license is granted (see
below and the Grant); no patent license is granted for commercial use.

Note on terminology: this is a SOURCE-AVAILABLE project, not an "open source"
project as defined by the Open Source Initiative. PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0
is not an OSI-approved license.

